snippet.title: Polygons of New York
snippet.description:
Behold the Rhombic Triacontahedron which links these two recent videos:

A new Rhombic Dodecahedron from Croatia!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xVBOlbjiHGI

The Best Square Square in New York
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yfR1Jkl5R8A

Rhombic Triacontahedron on Mathworld:
http://mathworld.wolfram.com/RhombicTriacontahedron.html

Here is the Exploded Rhombic Triacontahedron on Mike Deakin’s Shapeways page:
http://shpws.me/MhDT

I mentioned An Evening of Unnecessary Detail, a comedy show I do in London sometimes:
http://aneveningofunnecessarydetail.com/

In New York I was working with MoMath: http://momath.org/

Watch Mathologer’s video: How not to Die Hard with Math
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Oef3MHYEC0

And, I guess, you could watch Die Hard with a Vengeance…
https://www.amazon.com/Die-Hard-Vengeance-Bruce-Willis/dp/B001FVD65O/ref=sr_1_1?_encoding=UTF8&tag=stanupmath-21

CORRECTIONS:
So far, none yet! Let me know if you spot anything.

Music by Howard Carter
Design by Simon Wright

MATT PARKER: Stand-up Mathematician
Website: http://standupmaths.com/
Maths book: http://makeanddo4D.com/
Nerdy maths toys: http://mathsgear.co.uk/
